1.2 计算 Q 值¶

Q-Learning Q-Learning Value IterationPolicy Iteration-ValueUtility

Q-Learning Q - Q

$$ q(s_{t},a) = R_{t+1} + \gamma \times\max_a q(a,s_{t+1}) $$

- $(s_{t},a)$ $a$ $R_{t+1}$ $a$ $s_{t+1}$Q $\max_a q(a,s_{t+1})$$\gamma$

Q $alpha$ Q

$$ q(s_{t},a) = (1-\alpha) \times q(s_{t},a) + \alpha \times(R_{t+1} + \gamma \times\max_a q(a,s_{t+1})) $$

2 $q(s_{t},a)$

$s_1$ u $s_2$ Q u: -24r: -13d: -0.29l: +40$\gamma$ 0.9

$$ \begin{align} q(s_{t},a) & = R_{t+1} + \gamma \times\max_a q(a,s_{t+1}) \\ & =(-0.1) + (0.9)*(40) \\ & =(35.9) \end{align} $$

1.3 如何选择动作¶

  1. Q Q

epsilon-greedy Q

3 epsilon-greedy

In [1]:
import random

actions = ['u','r','d','l']
qline = {'u':1.2, 'r':-2.1, 'd':-24.5, 'l':27}
epsilon = 0.3 # 0.3

def choose_action(epsilon):
    
    action = None
    if random.random() < epsilon: # 
        action = random.choice(actions) # 
    else: 
        action = sorted(qline.items(), key=lambda x:(-x[1], x[0]))[0][0] #  Q 
    return action

# print(choose_action(epsilon))

from Runner import Runner

maze_size = (10, 10)
trap_number = 4
g = Maze(maze_size=maze_size,trap_number=trap_number)

for param in param_list:
    epoch = param['epoch']
    epsilon0 = param['epsilon0']
    alpha = param['alpha']
    gamma = param['gamma']
        
    r = Robot(g,alpha=alpha, epsilon0=epsilon0, gamma=gamma)
    r.set_status(learning=True)

    print('param{}'.format(param_list.index(param)))
    print('epoch:{}, epsilon0:{}, alpha:{}, gamma:{}, maze_size:{}, trap_number:{}'.format(epoch, epsilon0, alpha, gamma, maze_size, trap_number))
    runner = Runner(r, g)
    runner.run_training(epoch, display_direction=True)
    # runner.generate_movie(filename = "final1.mp4") # 
    
    runner.plot_results()
